,,, 5GHz Power Amplifier IC;SiGe;SE2537L;SiGe, 2537L, <????>;2;;16-pin QFN;3 mm x 3 mm x 0.9 mm; |flags= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=abgn |default_ssid=TRENDnet753_2.4GHz_XXXX, TRENDnet753_5GHz_XXXX |default_ssid_regex=^TRENDnet753_2.4GHz_[A-F0-9]{4}$,,, ^TRENDnet753_5GHz_[A-F0-9]{4}$ |default_ip= |default_user= |default_pass= |oui= |oui_eth= }} ''N600 High Power Dual Band PoE Access Point''
"7016A0507001 Ver: 1.00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. This is the same text found on the [[Senao CAP4200AG]] and derivative models. :The 2.4GHz radio (AR9382-AL1) is using two '''Microchip''' ('''SST''') SST12LP15A power amplifier ICs (marked "SST", "12LP15A", "152ASM"). :The 5GHz radio (AR9344-BC2A) is using two '''Skyworks''' ('''SiGe''') SE2537L / 2537L power amplifier ICs.
The Flash chip appears to be a MX25L12845EMI-10G (16 MB).
The power adapter in the FCC photos is a '''Powertron ELectronics Corp.''' PA1015-2I (100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.4A -> 12VDC, 1.25A).
